============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is the greenhouse effect?
A1: Greenhouse gases (CO2, methane) trap heat radiated from
     Earth's surface. Natural effect warms Earth; human
     emissions intensify it causing climate change.

Q2: What is osmosis?
A2: Osmosis is the movement of water across a semi-
     permeable membrane from high water concentration to low
     water concentration (high solute to low solute) until
     equilibrium.

Q3: What is the Big Bang?
A3: The Big Bang theory states the universe began from an
     extremely hot, dense point approximately 13.8 billion
     years ago and has been expanding ever since.

Q4: What is natural selection?
A4: Natural selection: individuals with traits better
     suited to their environment survive and reproduce more.
     Over many generations, these traits become more common
     in the population.

Q5: What is the water cycle?
A5: Water evaporates from oceans/lakes, rises and condenses
     into clouds, falls as precipitation, and flows back via
     rivers and groundwater. Driven by solar energy.

